   The Town of Los Altos Hills Recreation Program is accepting
   applications for its Summer 2001 Sports Camps. There are four sport
   camps being offered this summer.

   [ablbull1.gif] Mini-Hawks Multi-Sport Camp
       Session 1 - June 25-29, 9:00am-12:00pm
   Boys and Girls - Ages 4-7        Resident: $95    Non-Resident: $105
   [ablbull1.gif] Skyhawks Basketball Camp - July 16-20, 9:00am-3:00pm
   This camp is designed for the beginning and intermediate player.
   Campers will learn and refine the skills of passing, shooting,
   dribbling, and defense. Participants will receive a t-shirt, basketball
   and evaluation. Location: Bullis Elementary School.
   Boys and Girls - Ages 6-14    Resident: $105    Non-Resident: $115
   [ablbull1.gif] Skyhawks Soccer Camp - July 23-27, 9:00am-3:00pm
   Boys and Girls - Ages 6-14    Resident: $105    Non-Resident: $115
   [ablbull1.gif] Skyhawks Baseball Camp - August 6-10, 9:00am-3:00pm
   Boys and Girls - Ages 6-12    Resident: $105    Non-Resident: $115

   To enroll, download the application, registration and waiver forms via
   the link below, complete, sign and mail with your payment.

   Summer 2001 Sports Camp Application, Registration Form and Waiver
   (PDF-219kb)

   If you have any questions regarding these camps, please call (650)
   941-7222, ext. 306.


